e.native.cpu_variant=java` to evade NativeLoader's resources. This might be necessary since the test could impact the active status only and help to avoid unrelated NativeLoader dynamic access. I should set it before checking if it's ready.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test design**\\n\\nI'm thinking about creating a test using a custom ClassLoader to load an isolated copy of LICENSE and FipsStatus with a null ProtectionDomain. However, I remember the guideline about not using reflection directly unless necessary. To invoke methods on the isolated class, I’d probably need reflection, which feels like a dilemma. Additionally, dynamic loading of class names could lead to issues. I wonder if setting CodeSource to null via a SecurityManager is even feasible or reliable.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_2XItRLXq8zfEWjdJ6GTT6vEE|fc_0450f6a0c8d9113e0169f9eea361f881a0b7adb74e2cd758c9", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"dynamic-access|jacoco/effective|nativeTestCompile\" -n build.gradle tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/build.gradle forge gradle | head -200"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2467, "output": 1914, "cacheRead": 28160, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32541, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777987206605, "responseId": "resp_0450f6a0c8d9113e0169f9ee871bbc81a09870659fcf2e9155"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_2XItRLXq8zfEWjdJ6GTT6vEE|fc_0450f6a0c8d9113e0169f9eea361f881a0b7adb74e2cd758c9", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "forge/forge_metadata.py:2409:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage from the stored run metrics stats block.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2439:    \"\"\"Resolve the dynamic-access coverage report path for a new-library issue.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2445:        \"dynamic-access\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2446:        \"dynamic-access-coverage.json\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2451:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage directly from the generated report as a fallback.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2581:        \"Analyze the generated tests, metadata, stats, and dynamic-access report in this repository. \"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2585:        \"- Explain briefly why dynamic-access coverage is missing or still very low.\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2604:        f\"Automation completed for `{claimed_issue.issue_coordinates}`, but dynamic-access coverage remains \"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2606:        \"This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\n\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2608:        \"- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:3375:            pipeline_argv.append(\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\")\nforge/forge_metadata.py:5504:        \"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:5507:            \"Forwarded to the new-library pipeline. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access \"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:5508:            \"strategies even when no dynamic-access coverage is added.\"\nforge/utility_scripts/large_library_progress.py:246:        \"\"\"Record aggregate dynamic-access coverage.\"\"\"\nforge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:78:    \"\"\"Return True when the dynamic-access stats entry matches the expected object shape.\"\"\"\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:98:  [--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access] \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:123:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` keeps generated tests for dynamic-access workflows even if no dynamic-access call sites are covered.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:383:coordinates, active dynamic-access classes, source-context paths, and Gradle\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:418:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:449:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:456:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:478:For the detailed function-level notes and sequence diagram, see `docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md`.\nforge/utility_scripts/dynamic_access_report.py:160:        return \"All dynamic-access call sites are covered.\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:62:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:81:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:100:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:119:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:139:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:158:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:177:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:196:      \"dynamic-access-iter