[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring class loader issues**\n\nI’m troubleshooting an issue with a custom loader that relies on the parent’s getResourceAsStream for class bytes. During Gradle testing, I’m wondering if class resources may have been transformed. There's a concern with the FipsStatus.isReady method failing checksum validation because it uses LICENSE.class loaded by the custom loader. This loader doesn’t override getResource, meaning it defaults to the parent's implementation. I’m considering whether I should remove direct resource assertions from tests for clarity. Overall, there's room for improvement in coverage tracking, but I’m assessing if it's really necessary.\n\n**Revising static initialization sequence**\n\nI’m examining how the FipsSHS static initialization could fail due to duplicated bc classes before it reaches the checksum. I think calling getModuleHMAC first inside the isolated loader could help since it invokes getResourceName without loading the class. Our current code calls isReady first, which could lead to issues if FipsSHS class initialization fails. So, I’ll reorder things: calling getModuleHMAC before isReady could help maintain better coverage. Still, it's crucial that the tests ultimately pass, and I’m pondering the likelihood of isReady succeeding.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0450f6a0c8d9113e0169f9efc8facc81a0a7133104df6a9d09\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-e_XR13iNqgM895uBft39NkmAneFgj7bEOI7qa1eRAB_RYama_xGTRiuIVQ9X2sddHaen8Sd1rB_gQT3lSQRpnS5XuFTg4VBjHERtS7S68_KHjIxytEhWkY7LEyhxj2D2QK3i3XYMsViijcBP5gJ5SPKd9BX3788LXx2vqSf6tVm3b1SPArUP-9cdP9f4uv0xS4ER6WU6S2GbrxPpt_gQkbLjP-TQD9odurNE8JEF0z0H-1PG3CLLEmNNeMpB4fazyQgpHyYmltF5VgkIQj3hcPOAvLhsHHxVgDy_rSquZ3Cbq08qAgO4NTdxiLH9nFkFWbpP2RHnaRITUECw8aszDSL3HMyXm_PkekREd_JrQ1m_3F_6N5ioBe4hsasOLiRSRXJZWS1OrcZ7zyVQ-Y0KSOWrQphax4Hdw7P9RnOii7pqFooGw23qlJaCDwjOCeEndemsfRw7jOOzomyH