 it invokes getResourceName without loading the class. Our current code calls isReady first, which could lead to issues if FipsSHS class initialization fails. So, I’ll reorder things: calling getModuleHMAC before isReady could help maintain better coverage. Still, it's crucial that the tests ultimately pass, and I’m pondering the likelihood of isReady succeeding.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_cDrZcXVtTIQN7Igi1WDXe6Lh|fc_0450f6a0c8d9113e0169f9efd730dc81a089b2723973503733", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bc_fips/FipsStatusTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "        Method isReady = isolatedFipsStatus.getMethod(\"isReady\");\n        assertEquals(Boolean.TRUE, invokeStatic(isReady));\n\n        Method getStatusMessage = isolatedFipsStatus.getMethod(\"getStatusMessage\");\n        assertEquals(FipsStatus.READY, invokeStatic(getStatusMessage));\n\n        Method getModuleHmac = isolatedFipsStatus.getMethod(\"getModuleHMAC\");\n        byte[] hmac = assertInstanceOf(byte[].class, invokeStatic(getModuleHmac));\n        assertEquals(SHA256_HMAC_LENGTH, hmac.length);\n", "newText": "        Method getModuleHmac = isolatedFipsStatus.getMethod(\"getModuleHMAC\");\n        byte[] hmac = assertInstanceOf(byte[].class, invokeStatic(getModuleHmac));\n        assertEquals(SHA256_HMAC_LENGTH, hmac.length);\n\n        Method isReady = isolatedFipsStatus.getMethod(\"isReady\");\n        assertEquals(Boolean.TRUE, invokeStatic(isReady));\n\n        Method getStatusMessage = isolatedFipsStatus.getMethod(\"getStatusMessage\");\n        assertEquals(FipsStatus.READY, invokeStatic(getStatusMessage));\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1372, "output": 1222, "cacheRead": 44544, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 47138, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 177798752719