2HONewcYtiM7YgTasmTnYynDaJDj7L0_QWlWt2je29OIBUL3DfVWYlPgoV_KHKU5MrEkonO6Tyh5fnaXg07fORF72LyJdmJ20nSbl7oUMVDqPHInztKIG3fgwj_km0YmgE2lI7o4BxktjaJH09sZB8wr7NxCZW6n1dd98KOzaS2-CESPD4fggxsHT03WPQAWeQOs4_ozPPTxSzgHMnqNo6j5I6JD7Pb5hczUrmLN_ySTdL308j6-Re3Jwvyj6e6uGdr0ygBBcLTSdczs-lAaaB-CZphbq4YEDpxeOE1cUkU_Bzze02bXdiuc8EUU_z-oEUr-W_o9eyCRy3UMev0hQvnuORmsb5Qpu7NLIjmH6b2LLgCh83xEHYJZx5oDVxCV6lGlNToG-1379RZas6_1ySOIdx14s-z2biejel1D3Ynx8ddA4CQwolkyRGOjGuzJJusau2ZHWk6v2Y5DRr_Xqf-c3mCqfR8ZNuqWgttS4MtdKvh9KnKKgTlwG5AEWAzXT-PvBbVJ4XIGK8o0pDHqaxgMK01pH__RKD9PZD_WjqgJu4yh2mEToHo1RLSH3lSxYMOh7o0PFyTOCb9xemWMf7dw8zmPra0R2Rf9EbpnPdw1sGNvvSEh_svn4hISVjoYCe9__dn2z29MyXB1GYhhD-EjGpbppJLWeNWWFQOeqJUwc_2EsETatVovTrYAm20bNKZrvsMaFLHD65QdQxA-QKK62OrFQFTJh_C4TqZPCRyBFMKIvR4rxjiiczsuuxGiHXeDXpMpSLt86dLN0YioSpJCzNa6jdFm-v4Xo22mRA5GiKrDxJIpuOgsKz2E2Dt5rBxPUm74BkjDjEUGuxnePTKCWutUEPRAxsnuMPnPkiQWY4CfzHnqyVSOtiH1_Pm3YtrFpR0Z6ypyuBPKdgfxpanx2bF0sR4wZjgDZOEBEPP93oEyUz8LTnpEG_tOuBN5cCyolM=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class loading issues**\\n\\nI’m thinking that maybe the setSecurityManager method throws an UnsupportedOperationException, which I should catch and handle normally. For full coverage, it seems the JVM is likely supported. I wonder if I need a Class.forName call after setting the SecurityManager? The isReady method might already be set up. I’ll also consider the original reset being impossible and whether I can use FipsStatus.loadClass directly through MethodHandles and private lookup or by direct reflection.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class loading strategy**\\n\\nI'm thinking about isolating FipsStatus along with its nested anonymous classes, like FipsStatus$1, for privileged actions. It seems essential to load all FipsStatus child classes first and then delegate the rest. When I call loadClass for FipsSHS, I should also ensure it delegates to the parent. But what about the getMarker method with a null code source? I wonder if FipsStatus can use an isolated LICENSE. I might need to adjust how the loader works since it seems the existing child-first strategy could be overly complex.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing class loading process**\\n\\nI'm considering how it will load automatically via the same loader. I need to make sure to use loadUncached if the name equals or starts with FipsStatus$. I wonder if it's okay to have package-private access to NativeLoader, especially if a different loader is involved. I think maybe this could streamline the process, but I need to be careful about how those access levels interact. Let’s ensure everything is working as intended!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating exception handling methods**\\n\\nI'm thinking about implementing the `invokeIsReadyAllowingPackageBoundaryError` method. If an `InvocationTargetException` causes an `IllegalAccessError`, I'll have to return without doing anything further; otherwise, I should rethrow the error. This would occur after `Class.forName` has been called. If there's no error, I could assert true as normal. However, when dealing with native images, catching unsupported operations during testing might be required since `defineClass` could be unsupported.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_OtD4yDXqNHRglwwIM9XRd28E|fc_0450f6a0c8d9113e0169f9f0f2954881a0bb7bc1b43e9ae8cf", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bc_fips/FipsStatusTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.security.AllPermission;\nimport java.security.Permissions;\nimport java.security.ProtectionDomain;\n", "newText": "import java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.security.AllPermission;\nimport java.security.Permission;\nimport java.security.Permissions;\nimport java.security.ProtectionDomain;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    public void fipsStatusFallsBackToMarkerResourceLookupWithoutCodeSource() throws Exception {\n        String previousNativeVariant = System.getProperty(NATIVE_VARIANT_PROPERTY);\n        System.setProperty(NATIVE_VARIANT_PROPERTY, \"java\");\n        try {\n            assertStatusReadyFromIsolatedLoader();\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        } finally {\n            if (previousNativeVariant == null) {\n                System.clearProperty(NATIVE_VARIANT_PROPERTY);\n            } else {\n                System.setProperty(NATIVE_VARIANT_PROPERTY, previousNativeVariant);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void assertStatusReadyFromIsolatedLoader() throws Exception {\n        NullCodeSourceBouncyCastleLoader loader = new NullCodeSourceBouncyCastleLoader(\n                FipsStatusTest.class.getClassLoader());\n        Class<?> isolatedFipsStatus = loader.loadClass(\"org.bouncycastle.crypto.fips.FipsStatus\");\n\n        Method getModuleHmac = isolatedFipsStatus.getMethod(\"getModuleHMAC\");\n        byte[] hmac = assertInstanceOf(byte[].class, invokeStatic(getModuleHmac));\n        assertEquals(SHA256_HMAC_LENGTH, hmac.length);\n\n        Method isReady = isolatedFipsStatus.getMethod(\"isReady\");\n        assertEquals(Boolean.TRUE, invokeStatic(isReady));\n\n        Method getStatusMessage = isolatedFipsStatus.getMethod(\"getStatusMessage\");\n        assertEquals(FipsStatus.READY, invokeStatic(getStatusMessage));\n    }\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    public void fipsStatusFallsBackToMarkerResourceLookupWhenProtectionDomainIsDenied() {\n        SecurityManager previousSecurityManager = System.getSecurityManager();\n        boolean installed = installSecurityManager(new DenyProtectionDomainSecurityManager());\n        try {\n            byte[] hmac = FipsStatus.getModuleHMAC();\n            asse